==English==

===Etymology===
Contraction of [[have|(ha)ve]].

===Suffix===
''''ve'''
# [[Have]] (''marking the [[perfect]], or [[retrospective]], tense'')
# (''some dialects'') Have, [[possess]].

===Related terms===
* [['d]] (''past tense'')
* [['s]] (''third person'')

===Usage note===
*In most dialects, -''''ve''' is only used to mark the perfect tense ("''I've done something.''", "''I have done something.''"), and not to signify possession ("''I have something.''"). Some dialects, however, use -''''ve''' for both.

